      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:5:3:127:4",
      "text": [
        " قَالَ أَمِيرُ الْمُؤْمِنِينَ ( عليه السلام ) فِي بَرِيرَةَ ثَلَاثٌ مِنَ السُّنَنِ حِينَ أُعْتِقَتْ فِي التَّخْيِيرِ وَ فِي الصَّدَقَةِ وَ فِي الْوَلَاءِ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Humeyd Bin Ziyad, from Ibn Sama’at, from someone else, from Aban, from the one who narrated it, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘Amir Al-Momineen<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘Regarding Bureyra, there are three Sunnahs when she was emancipated – regarding the choice, and regarding the charity, and regarding the mastership’."
        ]
      }
